Labour inspectors say a risk assessment must be done at vulnerable workplaces and if social distancing can't be implemented, alternative plans must be made. JOHANNESBURG - Labour Minister Thulas Nxesi will brief the public on South Africa's back-to-work readiness. The economy will see a slight pick-up in activity with around 1.5-million people returning to work as lockdown restrictions ease. READ: South Africa enters into level 4 lockdown Public transport can be utilised at all times of the day, but with restrictions. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.